The silly thing is they already have NSArray (immutable) and NSMutableArray (mutable) on the Objective-C side. So you&#x27;d expect anybody working on putting this stuff together to be familiar with this. I guess the four possibilities in Objective-C are:<p><pre><code>    NSArray *const p;
    NSMutableArray *const p;
    NSArray *p;
    NSMutableArray *p;
</code></pre>
(&quot;const NSArray *p&quot; and so on makes no sense, as I understand it - the Objective side of Objective-C being not big on const.)
